ANTHRAX - RUSSIA (03): (VOLGOGRAD) HUMAN, LIVESTOCK, CONFIRMED
**************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 13 Aug 2014
Source: RIA Novosti [in Russian, trans., edited]
http://ria.ru/society/20140813/1019833098.html


Volgograd experts have established the diagnosis of anthrax from a resident in the village of Molokanovsky Ilmensky rural settlement over the weekend [9-10 Aug 2014]. In the Oktyabrsky district of Volgograd region presently under quarantine. According to the regional government, quarantine was established because of the threat of anthrax introduced in this district of Volgograd region.

The infection occurred as a result of the slaughtering a bullock at home. The owner of a farmstead did not use the services of slaughterhouses and the meat was sold to dealers. At the moment a man has been admitted to the infectious diseases hospital in Volgograd.

"From 11 to 26 Aug 2014 the Oktyabrsky district will be under quarantine due to the fact that a local resident has been confirmed with a diagnosis of anthrax. However, concern about the possible further spread of the disease is unnecessary -- specialized services have taken all the necessary precautions," -- said an official statement. In the quarantine area the following have been banned: the movement of livestock; removal of hay, roots and other forage; the use of milk from sick and suspect animals; and slaughtering them for meat. Veterinary Service has deployed health education teams among the local population.

[Byline: Ulyana Grebennikova]

